Package camzup.core

Class Mesh3

java.lang.Object
camzup.core.EntityData
camzup.core.Mesh
camzup.core.Mesh3
All Implemented Interfaces:
IEntityData, IMesh, IUtils, java.lang.Cloneable
public class Mesh3
extends Mesh
Organizes data needed to draw a three dimensional shape using vertices and faces. Given that a mesh is primarily a collection of references, it is initialized with null arrays (coordinates, texture coordinates and indices). These are not final, and so can be reassigned.

    • insetFace

      public int[][][] insetFace​(int faceIdx, float fac)
      Insets a face by calculating its centroid then easing from the face's vertices toward the centroid by the amount, expected to be in the range [0.0, 1.0] . When the amount is less than 0.0, the face remains unchanged; when the amount is greater than 1.0, then the face is subdivided by centroid.
      Parameters:
      faceIdx - the face index
      fac - the inset amount
      Returns:
      the new face indices

    • subdivFaceCentroid

      public int[][][] subdivFaceCentroid​(int faceIdx)
      Subdivides a convex face by calculating its centroid, subdividing each of its edges with one cut to create a midpoint, then connecting the midpoints to the centroid. This generates a quadrilateral for the number of edges in the face.
      Parameters:
      faceIdx - the face index
      Returns:
      the new face indices

    • subdivFaceFan

      public int[][][] subdivFaceFan​(int faceIdx)
      Subdivides a convex face by calculating its centroid, then connecting its vertices to the centroid. This generates a triangle for the number of edges in the face.
      Parameters:
      faceIdx - the face index
      Returns:
      the new face indices

    • subdivFaceInscribe

      public int[][][] subdivFaceInscribe​(int faceIdx)
      Subdivides a convex face by cutting each of its edges once to create a midpoint, then connecting them. This generates peripheral triangles and a new central face with the same number of edges as the original. This is best suited to meshes made of triangles.
      Parameters:
      faceIdx - the face index
      Returns:
      the new face indices

    • fromObj

      public static Mesh3 fromObj​(java.lang.String[] lines, Mesh3 target)
      Creates a mesh from an array of strings representing a WaveFront obj file.

      Files supplied to this parser should always include information for coordinates, texture coordinates and normals.

      Material information is not parsed from the file, as Processing would not accurately recreate it.
      Parameters:
      lines - the String tokens
      target - the output mesh
      Returns:
      the mesh

    • uniformData

      public static Mesh3 uniformData​(Mesh3 source, Mesh3 target)
      Restructures the mesh so that each face index refers to unique data, indifferent to redundancies. As a consequence, coordinates and texture coordinate are of equal length and face indices are easier to read and understand. Useful for making a mesh similar to those in Unity. Similar to 'ripping' vertices or 'tearing' edges in Blender.
      Parameters:
      source - the source mesh
      target - the target mesh
      Returns:
      the mesh

    • uvSphere

      public static Mesh3 uvSphere​(int longitudes, int latitudes, Mesh3 target)
      Creates a UV sphere. The longitudes, or meridians, run through the sphere's poles, and correspond to the azimuth in spherical coordinates. The latitudes correspond to the inclination. Supplying half as many latitudes as longitudes will provide the best results.
      Parameters:
      longitudes - the longitudes
      latitudes - the latitudes
      target - the output mesh
      Returns:
      the sphere
